<p> <h3>Definitions</h3>
<p style="color: lightgreen;"> Markup: Text with special meaning, normally uses tags (i.e italics, bold)
<br> Whitespace: Spaces, tabs, and line breaks in html, need to use tags to create the effect on the browser.
<br> Types of elements: block, inline, void
<br> Attribute: added inside start tag, giving element more meaning; consists of: name = "value"

</p> <h4>Notes</h4>
<ul>
  <li>URLs require http, https, file as the protocol
  <li> images can use relative URLs, pay attn to syntax <img src="Image URL here" alt="A description of the image">
  <li> help : <a href="https://validator.w3.org/nu/#textarea">validator</a>
  <li> selector (html) + declaration (how to modify element) = CSS ruleset
</ul>

